name: gomigration
description: Lightweight and extensible database migration library for Go, designed with simplicity and flexibility in mind

name: goevent
description: A type-safe, flexible event bus for Go, providing an elegant wrapper around EventBus with enhanced error handling, synchronization, and per-event waiting capabilities.

name: goqueue
description: A lightweight, interface-driven queue library that makes it easy to add background job processing to your Go applications.

name: gomail
description: A high-performance Go wrapper for `gopkg.in/gomail.v2` with connection pooling, persistent connections, and bulk sending capabilities.

name: gostorage
description: A flexible, extensible storage abstraction layer for Go that supports multiple backends including local filesystem and AWS S3.

name: goauth
description: Pluggable authentication for Go. Build username/password or JWT-based auth with a simple strategy interface, a configurable JWT access-token + refresh-token issuer, and typed errors for clean, predictable error handling.

name: govalidator
description: A powerful and flexible Go package designed to simplify and enhance data validation for your applications. Built upon the robust github.com/go-playground/validator/v10 library

name: goinit
description: A command-line tool to quickly initialize Go projects with pre-configured architectures and templates.
